  description: "concurrent.futures ThreadPoolExecutor and Executor method __qualname__ checks in cfexecident122 namespace — wave 256 theme: ThreadPoolExecutor.submit.__qualname__.__eq__('ThreadPoolExecutor.submit')==True (len=25: 'ThreadPoolExecutor.'=19+'submit'=6=25); ThreadPoolExecutor.submit.__qualname__.__len__()==25; ThreadPoolExecutor.submit.__class__.__name__.__eq__('function')==True (Python-defined in thread.py); ThreadPoolExecutor.shutdown.__qualname__.__eq__('ThreadPoolExecutor.shutdown')==True (len=27: 'ThreadPoolExecutor.'=19+'shutdown'=8=27, longest in spec); ThreadPoolExecutor.shutdown.__qualname__.__len__()==27; Executor.submit.__qualname__.__eq__('Executor.submit')==True (len=15: 'Executor.'=9+'submit'=6=15; defined in _base.py and raises NotImplementedError as abstract); Executor.submit.__qualname__.__len__()==15; Executor.map.__qualname__.__eq__('Executor.map')==True (len=12: 'Executor.'=9+'map'=3=12, shortest in spec); Executor.map.__qualname__.__len__()==12; Executor.shutdown.__qualname__.__eq__('Executor.shutdown')==True (len=17: 'Executor.'=9+'shutdown'=8=17); Executor.shutdown.__qualname__.__len__()==17; contrast with ThreadPoolExecutor.shutdown len=27 (10 more chars due to 'ThreadPoolExecutor.'=19 vs 'Executor.'=9 prefix); verified with Python 3.14.3"
