  description: "concurrent.futures.ProcessPoolExecutor.__qualname__.__len__() == 19 — ProcessPoolExecutor.__qualname__ is 'ProcessPoolExecutor' (19 chars: 'Process'=7+'Pool'=4+'Executor'=8=19); ProcessPoolExecutor is one char longer than ThreadPoolExecutor (19 vs 18) because 'Process'=7 > 'Thread'=6; ProcessPoolExecutor.__module__ is 'concurrent.futures.process'; ProcessPoolExecutor.__bases__[0].__name__ is 'Executor' (same direct base as ThreadPoolExecutor); ProcessPoolExecutor.__mro__.__len__() is 3 (same depth as ThreadPoolExecutor); qualname lengths ranking in spec: Future=6 < Executor=8 < ThreadPoolExecutor=18 < ProcessPoolExecutor=19; NEW in extra122: first standalone ProcessPoolExecutor qualname length invariant in cfexecident122 namespace; wave 256; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  category: identity
