invariant concurrent_futures_extra122.Executor_mro_len_2:
  description: "concurrent.futures.Executor.__mro__.__len__() == 2 — Executor.__mro__ is [Executor, object] (2 elements); Executor is the abstract base class from which both ThreadPoolExecutor and ProcessPoolExecutor inherit; its minimal 2-element MRO contrasts with the 3-element MROs of ThreadPoolExecutor and ProcessPoolExecutor ([Subclass, Executor, object]); Executor.__module__ is 'concurrent.futures._base'; Executor.__qualname__ is 'Executor' (len=8); Executor.__bases__[0].__name__ is 'object'; concurrent.futures.Future also has MRO length 2 ([Future, object]); both base classes (Executor and Future) are defined in _base.py and have the same 2-element MRO depth; NEW in extra122: first standalone Executor MRO length invariant in cfexecident122 namespace; wave 256; verified with Python 3.14.3"
