invariant concurrent_futures_extra122.Future_qualname_len_6:
  description: "concurrent.futures.Future.__qualname__.__len__() == 6 — Future.__qualname__ is 'Future' (6 chars); this is the shortest class qualname in this spec: Future=6 < Executor=8 < ThreadPoolExecutor=18 < ProcessPoolExecutor=19; concurrent.futures.Future is Python-defined in _base.py — its methods (result, cancel, done, exception, set_result, add_done_callback) are Python 'function' class, unlike asyncio.Future whose methods are C-level 'method_descriptor'; Future.__module__ is 'concurrent.futures._base'; Future.__mro__.__len__() is 2 ([Future, object]); Future.__bases__[0].__name__ is 'object'; NEW in extra122: first standalone concurrent.futures.Future qualname length invariant in cfexecident122 namespace; wave 256; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  category: identity
