invariant concurrent_futures_extra122.ThreadPoolExecutor_shutdown_qualname_len_27:
  description: "concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor.shutdown.__qualname__.__len__() == 27 — ThreadPoolExecutor.shutdown.__qualname__ is 'ThreadPoolExecutor.shutdown' (27 chars: 'ThreadPoolExecutor.'=19+'shutdown'=8=27); this is the longest method qualname in this spec; compare method qualname lengths: Executor.map=12, Executor.submit=15, Executor.shutdown=17, ThreadPoolExecutor.submit=25, ThreadPoolExecutor.shutdown=27; the 19-char 'ThreadPoolExecutor.' prefix (class name + dot) makes all ThreadPoolExecutor method qualnames significantly longer than Executor method qualnames (which use 9-char 'Executor.' prefix); ThreadPoolExecutor.shutdown.__class__.__name__ is 'function' (Python-defined); shutdown() gracefully shuts down the executor, optionally waiting for futures to complete; NEW in extra122: first standalone ThreadPoolExecutor.shutdown qualname length invariant in cfexecident122 namespace; wave 256; verified with Python 3.14.3"
  category: identity
  kind: python_call_eq
  function: "concurrent.futures.ThreadPoolExecutor.shutdown.__qualname__.__len__"
